ades]]\n[[Category:1090s conflicts]]\n[[Category:History of Antioch]]\n[[Category:Wars involving the Fatimid Caliphate]]\n[[Category:Wars involving the Byzantine Empire]]\n[[Category:Wars involving the Holy Roman Empire]]\n[[Category:Wars involving the Republic of Genoa]]\n[[Category:Wars involving the Republic of Pisa]]\n[[Category:Wars involving France]]\n[[Category:Wars involving Armenia]]\n[[Category:11th century in the Fatimid Caliphate]]\n[[Category:1090s in the Byzantine Empire]]\n[[Category:1090s in Asia]]\n[[Category:1090s in Europe]]\n[[Category:1090s in the Kingdom of Jerusalem]]\n", "name_user": "Sheldknight76", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/First_Crusade"}
{"title_page": "List of young adult writers", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n<!--- IMPORTANT: Please do not add entries to this page unless the author \u2014 or one of the books mentioned \u2014 has a separate article in Wikipedia. If there is no article although the author is notable, please consider creating or requesting it (see Wikipedia:Requested articles). --->\nThis is a list of notable [[young adult fiction|writers]] whose readership is predominantly teenagers or young adults, or adult fiction writers who have published significant works intended for teens/young adults. Examples of the author's more notable works are given here.\n{{inc-lit}}\n\n{{compact ToC|num=yes}}\n\n==A==\n[[File:Renee Ahdieh 2017.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Renee Ahdieh]]]]\n*[[Joan Abelove]]: ''Go and Come Back'', ''Saying It Out Loud'', ''Lost and Found''\n*[[Hailey Abbott]]: ''The Secrets of Boys'', ''Summer Boys'', ''The Bridesmaid'', ''The Perfect Boy''\n*[[Richard Adams]]: ''[[Watership Down]]'', ''[[Shardik]]'', ''[[The Plague Dogs]]''\n*[[Alexandra Adornetto]]: ''Halo'', ''Hades'', ''Heaven''\n*[[Renee Ahdieh]]: ''[[The Wrath & the Dawn]]'', ''[[Flame in the Mist]]''\n*[[Becky Albertalli]]: ''[[Simon vs. the Homo Sapiens Agenda]]'', ''[[The Upside of Unrequited]]'', ''Leah on the Offbeat''\n*[[Louisa May Alcott]]: ''[[Little Women]]'', ''[[Jo's Boys]]'', ''[[Eight Cousins]]''\n*[[Lloyd Alexander]]:  ''[[The Prydain Chronicles]]'', ''[[Westmark (novel)|Westmark]]'', ''[[The Kestrel]]'', ''[[The Beggar Queen]]''\n*[[Sherman Alexie]]: '' [[The Absolutely True Diary of a Part-Time Indian]]''\n*[[Isabel Allende]]: ''[[City of the Beasts]]'', ''[[Kingdom of the Golden Dragon]]'', ''[[Forest of the Pygmies]]''\n*[[David Almond]]:  ''Kit's Wilderness'', ''[[Heaven Eyes]]'', ''[[Clay (novel)|Clay]]''\n*[[Elaine M. Alphin]]:  ''[[Counterfeit Son]]''\n*[[Julia Alvarez]]:  ''[[How the Garc\u00eda Girls Lost Their Accents]]'', ''Yo!'', ''Before We Were Free''\n*[[Adi Alsaid]]: ''Let's Get Lost'', ''Never Always Sometimes''\n*[[Laurie Halse Anderson]]:  ''[[Speak (Anderson novel)|Speak]]'', ''[[Fever 1793]]'', ''[[Catalyst (novel)|Catalyst]]'', ''Prom'', ''Twisted'', ''[[Wintergirls]]''\n*[[M. T. Anderson]]:  ''[[Feed (Anderson novel)|Feed]]'', ''[[The Pox Party]]''\n*[[V. C. Andrews]]: ''[[Flowers in the Attic]]''\n*[[Anthony (writer)|Anthony]]: ''A Journey, through Time, with Anthony''\n*[[Kim Antieau]]: ''Mercy, Unbound''\n*[[Allen Appel]]: ''Twice Upon a Time''\n*[[Jules Archer]]: ''The Plot to Seize the White House'', ''The Incredible Sixties'', ''Treason in America''\n*[[Jennifer Armentrout]]: ''Covenant'' series, ''Lux'' series, ''Dark Elements'' series, ''Cursed''\n*[[Kelley Armstrong]]: ''[[Darkest Powers]]''\n*[[Jay Asher]]: ''[[Thirteen Reasons Why]]'', ''[[The Future of Us]]''\n*[[Amelia Atwater-Rhodes]]: ''[[Den of Shadows]] series'',  ''[[The Kiesha'ra Series|Kiesha'ra]] series''\n*[[Victoria Aveyard]]: ''[[Red Queen (novel)|Red Queen]]''\n*[[Edward Irving Wortis|Avi]]:  ''[[Nothing But the Truth (novel)|Nothing But the Truth]]'', ''[[The True Confessions of Charlotte Doyle]]'', ''[[Crispin: The Cross of Lead]]''\n\n==B==\n[[File:JudyBlume2009(cropped).jpg|thumb|[[Judy Blume]]]]\n* [[Natalie Babbitt]]: ''[[Tuck Everlasting]]''\n*[[Helen Bailey]]: ''Electra Brown'' series\n*[[Leigh Bardugo]]: ''[[Shadow and Bone]]''\n*[[T. A. Barron]]:  ''The Ancient One''\n*[[John Barrowman]] and [[Carole Barrowman]]: ''[[Hollow Earth (novel)|Hollow Earth]]''\n*[[Lynda Barry]], cartoonist, graphic novelist\n*[[Cat Bauer]]:  ''Harley's Ninth'', ''Harley, Like a Person''\n*[[Joan Bauer (novelist)|Joan Bauer]]:  ''Rules of the Road'', ''Squashed'', ''Stand Tall'', ''[[Hope Was Here]]''\n*[[Michael Gerard Bauer]]: ''[[The Running Man (Bauer novel)|The Running Man]]'', ''[[Don't Call Me Ishmael]]''\n*[[L. Frank Baum]]: ''[[Aunt Jane's Nieces]]'' series\n*[[John and Patricia Beatty|Patricia Beatty]]: ''Lupita Ma\u00f1ana'', ''[[Charley Skeda