 (novel)|Story of a Girl]]'', ''How to Save a Life'', ''Once Was Lost''\n*[[Gabrielle Zevin]]: ''[[Elsewhere (Zevin novel)|Elsewhere]]'', ''Memoirs of a Teenage Amnesiac''\n*[[Cecily von Ziegesar]]: ''[[Gossip Girl (novel series)|Gossip Girl]]'' series, ''[[The It Girl (book series)|It Girl]]'' series\n*[[Paul Zindel]]:  ''[[The Pigman]]'', ''[[The Pigman's Legacy]]'', ''[[My Darling, My Hamburger]]'', ''[[Pardon Me, You're Stepping on My Eyeball!]]'', ''[[Confessions of a Teenage Baboon]]''\n*[[Markus Zusak]]: ''[[The Book Thief]]'', ''[[The Messenger (Zusak novel)|The Messenger]]''\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal |Children's and young adult literature}}\n* [[List of children's literature writers]]\n* [[Lists of writers]] \n* [[List of teen films]]\n* [[Teen drama]]\n* [[List of books written by children or teenagers|List of books written by teenagers]]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Young adult writers}}\n[[Category:Lists of writers]]\n[[Category:Writers of young adult literature| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n<!--- IMPORTANT: Please do not add entries to this page unless the author \u2014 or one of the books mentioned \u2014 has a separate article in Wikipedia. If there is no article although the author is notable, please consider creating or requesting it (see Wikipedia:Requested articles). --->\nThis is a list of notable [[young adult fiction|writers]] whose readership is predominantly teenagers or young adults, or adult fiction writers who have published significant works intended for teens/young adults. Examples of the author's more notable works are given here.\n{{inc-lit}}\n\n{{compact ToC|num=yes}}\n\n==A==\n[[File:Renee Ahdieh 2017.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Renee Ahdieh]]]]\n*[[Joan Abelove]]: ''Go and Come Back'', ''Saying It Out Loud'', ''Lost and Found''\n*[[Hailey Abbott]]: ''The Secrets of Boys'', ''Summer Boys'', ''The Bridesmaid'', ''The Perfect Boy''\n*[[Richard Adams]]: ''[[Watership Down]]'', ''[[Shardik]]'', ''[[The Plague Dogs]]''\n*